### Install the "REST Client" extension in VS Code, then click "Send Request" above each block.
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080/api/threats

### 1. Submit a new threat (run scripts/find_nonce.py first to get a valid nonce)
POST {{baseUrl}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "indicatorValue": "198.51.100.42",
  "indicatorType": "IP",
  "threatDescription": "Brute force attempts detected on SSH port 22.",
  "submittedByNode": "NODE-NODE-772A",
  "proofOfWorkNonce": 56723
}

### 2. Get all threats
GET {{baseUrl}}

### 3. Get only VERIFIED threats (what Member 3's Python agent will call)
GET {{baseUrl}}?status=VERIFIED

### 4. Get a single threat by id
GET {{baseUrl}}/1

### 5. Cast votes until it crosses the consensus threshold (min-votes=3, threshold=70%)
POST {{baseUrl}}/1/vote
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "votingNode": "NODE-BETA-001",
  "voteValue": true
}

###
POST {{baseUrl}}/1/vote
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "votingNode": "NODE-GAMMA-002",
  "voteValue": true
}

###
POST {{baseUrl}}/1/vote
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "votingNode": "NODE-DELTA-003",
  "voteValue": true
}

### 6. Try voting twice from the same node - should get a 400 error
POST {{baseUrl}}/1/vote
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "votingNode": "NODE-BETA-001",
  "voteValue": true
}
